AUDIO: 'Gemini 2.5 Pro or Gro 4, they all use what is called chain of thought, which is like writing down your thoughts step by step to help solve these problems. But chain of thought has a ton of'

[34:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'downsides. It\'s really easy for it to mess up if one step goes wrong. Plus, it needs a ton of training data and it\'s very slow because it needs extra time to generate those steps. So to fix these'

[34:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'issues, the researchers in this paper suggest this new architecture called hierarchical reasoning model. This is designed to be like the human brain which handles thinking in different'

[35:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'layers or hierarchies and also at different speeds. This is what they called multi-time scale. So for example, your brain has some big picture ideas that it needs to plan slowly but also'

[35:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some detail oriented areas that work very quickly. So this hierarchical reasoning model is a recurrent architecture. In other words, it loops information back to itself for deeper'

[35:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'processing. Now, again, this paper is super technical. It\'s just a ton of formulas like this. But basically, this recurrent architecture allows it to do a lot of complex calculations without becoming unstable during training or'

[35:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'without using much time or compute. So, unlike other top AI models out there, this one solves these really complex problems in just one quick pass. There\'s no need to think or reason for as long.'

[35:57] [scene:talk]
